"{\n  \"text\": \"Hi everybody. I'm always going on about fermented foods and living foods and this and that, and why not just take a probiotic pill? What's the difference? Well, I had gone off in another video about how the bio probiotic pills lack biodiversity. But another factor in them is that it has a tough time getting through your stomach to your gut. Your gut has a protective chamber before it the stomach, which is full of acid, which kills as much as it can to give your little your gut a little protection. When you hide the bacteria, the healthy bacteria within roughage, roughage is only partially broken down. So this roughage makes it through the stomach and to the colon with its bacteria intact. And that's something that's very difficult to do for any other type of bacteria. Basically, you have to hide your bacteria in your roughage in order to get it to your colon. This is why sometimes probiotics and probiotic based drinks don't have the same effect because they don't make it through the stomach alive. Anyway, thanks y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hi everybody.\",\n      \"start\": 0.56,\n      \"end\": 1.76,\n      \"duration\": 1.2,\n      \"confidence\": 0.983,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" Hi\",\n          \"start\": 0.56,\n          \"end\": 0.88,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 0.995\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 1.12,\n          \"end\": 1.28,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 1.28,\n          \"end\": 1.52,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 1.52,\n          \"end\": 1.68,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \".\",\n          \"start\": 1.68,\n          